{"lemma":"عُنْقُ","slug":"عُنْقُ","root":"ع.ن.ق","root_slug":"ع-ن-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ن-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عُنْقُ","root":"عنق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":9},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30784","n30788","n30789","n30790","n30791"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D9%86%D9%92%D9%82%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"neck"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cervix uteri"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pedicle"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a company of men"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"length of the neck"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a pace of the camel"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to embrace, to go around or grab the neck of"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"inclined towards, solicitous for"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"masculine/feminine plural of أَعْنَق (ʔaʕnaq)","tags":["feminine","form-of","masculine","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕu.nuq/","/ʕunq/","/ʕa.naq/","/ʕan.na.qa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30784","headword_ar":"عَنِقَ","root":"Enq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanaqN","text_ar":"عَنَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, TK)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, long in the neck."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, TK. [The verb in this sense is said in the TA to be like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariHa","text_ar":"فَرِحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but in two instances in the same it is written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanuqa","text_ar":"عَنُقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the same inf. n., and expl. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, long and thick in the neck."},{"kind":"text","text":"]) ―         -b2-  [Golius has assigned to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanaqa","text_ar":"عَنَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(an unknown verb) two significations belonging to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEn~q","text_ar":"تعنّق"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30788","headword_ar":"عُنْقٌ","root":"Enq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuqN","text_ar":"عُنُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence, in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30789","headword_ar":"عَنَقٌ","root":"Enq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Length of the neck."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K. [See also 1.]) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stretching pace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hastening and stretching pace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the horse or the like, and of camels: (S, O, K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pace with wide steps:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain quick pace, with wide steps:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEonaqa","text_ar":"اَعْنَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaniyqN","text_ar":"عَنِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (O, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaba Als~ayora","text_ar":"نَصَبَ السَّيْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasaja","text_ar":"وَسَجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] A rájiz (Abu-n-Nejm, TA) says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yaA naAqa siyriY EanaqFA fasiyHaA\n                      \n                     \n                        A_ilYa sulayomaAna fatasotariyHaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O she-camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA naAqa","text_ar":"يَا نَاقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yA naAqapu","text_ar":"يا نَاقَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"go a stretching-pace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with wide steps, to Suleyman, that thou mayest find rest"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA","Mgh","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n30790","headword_ar":"عُنَقٌ","root":"Enq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30791","headword_ar":"عُنُقٌ","root":"Enq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunoqN","text_ar":"عُنْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K, &c.,) the former of the dial. of El-Hijáz, and the latter of the dial. of Temeem, (Msb,) the latter said by Sb to be a contraction of the former, (TA,) [which is the more common,] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaniyqN","text_ar":"عَنِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunaqN","text_ar":"عُنَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, [in which it is implied that these two have all the significations assigned by its author to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuqN","text_ar":"عُنُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunoqN","text_ar":"عُنْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) but [SM says] none of the leading lexicologists has mentioned these two, in what I have seen, (TA,) [adding that he had found in the O"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaniyqu","text_ar":"العَنِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEanaqu","text_ar":"العَنَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which he supposes the author of the K to have thought to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEunuqu","text_ar":"العُنُقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neck;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part that forms a connection between the head and the body;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqabapN","text_ar":"رَقَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiydN","text_ar":"جِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) [but see these two words:] masc. and fem.; (S, O, K;) generally masc., (IB, Msb, * TA,) but in the dial. of El- Hijáz fem.; (Msb;) or, as some say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunoqN","text_ar":"عُنْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is masc., and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuqN","text_ar":"عُنُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is fem.: (TA:) the pl. (i. e. of the first and second, TA) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEonaAqN","text_ar":"اَعْنَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, S, O, Msb, K,) the only pl. form. (Sb, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eunuqu AlHay~api","text_ar":"عُنُقُ الحَيَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A star"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the neck of the constellation Serpens."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eunuqu Al$~ujaAEi","text_ar":"عُنُقُ الشُّجَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The star a in the hinder part of the neck of the constellation Hydra:"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfrodu","text_ar":"الفرْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eunuqu Alr~aHimi","text_ar":"عُنُقُ الرَّحِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The neck of the womb;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the slender part of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rHm","text_ar":"رحم"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"froj","text_ar":"فرْج"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eunuqu Alkari$i","text_ar":"عُنُقُ الكَرِشِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lowest portion of the stomach of a ruminant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHát, O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aliqbapu","text_ar":"الِقبَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (AHát, O.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEonaAqu Aln~axoli","text_ar":"اَعْنَاقُ النَّخْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The trunks of palm-trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qSr","text_ar":"قصر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a liloHab~i A^aEonaAqahu","text_ar":"مَدَّ لِلْحَبِّ اَعْنَاقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of seedproduce [or corn], means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The internodal portions of its culms appeared."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHonaqa","text_ar":"اَحْنَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEonaAqu Alr~iyHi","text_ar":"اَعْنَاقُ الرِّيحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What have risen of the dust that is raised by the wind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA.) [The phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qd rA^s AEnAqu AlryH","text_ar":"قد راس اعناقُ الريح"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned by Freytag as from the K, is a strange mistake.] ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxoruju EunuqN","text_ar":"يَخْرُجُ عُنُقٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Aln~aAri","text_ar":"مِنَ النَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2176},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will issue from the fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Hell"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b9-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaraja mina Aln~ahori EunuqN","text_ar":"خَرَجَ مِنَ النَّهْرِ عُنُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A current of water issued from the river,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rivulet."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, TA.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eunuqu","text_ar":"عُنُقُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~ayofi","text_ar":"الصَّيْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~itaA='i","text_ar":"الشِّتَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The first part"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of summer"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of winter"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eunuqu Als~in~i","text_ar":"عُنُقُ السِّنِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The first part of the age"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man as counted by years]: IAar says, I said to an Arab of the desert,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamo A^ataY Ealayoka","text_ar":"كَمْ اَتَى عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How many"},{"kind":"text","text":"years"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have passed over thee?"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and he answered,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*otu biEunuqi","text_ar":"اَخَذْتُ بِعُنُقِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~it~iyna","text_ar":"السِّتِّينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have entered upon"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the first part of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"st~yn","text_ar":"ستّين"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sixtieth"},{"kind":"text","text":"year]: and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEonaAqN","text_ar":"اَعْنَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna *`lika EalaY Eunuqi Ald~ahori","text_ar":"كَانَ ذٰلِكَ عَلَى عُنُقِ الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_isolaAmi","text_ar":"الاـِسْلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That was in the old"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"early"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of time"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (O, K, TA) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of El-Islám"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b11-  [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuqN","text_ar":"عُنُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. signifies (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an elevated and elongated tract of sand, or the like: see the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEonaAq","text_ar":"اَعْنَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the last sentence of this art.] ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkalaAmu yaA^oxu*u baEoDuhu","text_ar":"الكَلَامُ يَاْخُذُ بَعْضُهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA^aEonaAqi baEoDK","text_ar":"بِاَعْنَاقِ بَعْضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEunuqi baEoDK","text_ar":"بِعُنُقِ بَعْضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are tropical phrases [app. meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"language, is coherent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compact"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo EunuqN A_ilayoka","text_ar":"هُمْ عُنُقٌ اـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are inclining to thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expecting thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) or, accord. to Az,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they have advanced towards thee with their company"},{"kind":"text","text":"[agreeably with what next follows]. (TA.) ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuqN","text_ar":"عُنُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A company"},{"kind":"text","text":"of men: (O, K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a numerous company"},{"kind":"text","text":"of men: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a preceding company"},{"kind":"text","text":"of men: and is masc.: (TA:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heads,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chiefs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA,) of men; (O, TA;) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great ones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobles."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faZal~ato A^aEonaAquhumo lahaA","text_ar":"فَظَلَّتْ اَعْنَاقُهُمْ لَهَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaADiEiyna","text_ar":"خَاضِعِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxvi. 3], is expl. as meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And their great ones"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their chiefs"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall continue submissive to it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their companies:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the pret. is here used in the sense of the future: (O, TA:) or, as some say, the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their necks."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xDE","text_ar":"خضع"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY EunuqK mina Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"فِى عُنُقٍ مِنَ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came in a company of men."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA=' Alqawomu EunuqFA EunuqFA","text_ar":"جَا=ء القَوْمُ عُنُقًا عُنُقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people came in"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"successive"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"parties;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as Az says, each, or every, company of them being termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eunuq","text_ar":"عُنُق"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gradually, party by party."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo EunuqN Ealayohi","text_ar":"هُمْ عُنُقٌ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are a company,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, combined against him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yazaAlu Aln~aAsu muxotalifapF A^aEonaAquhumo fiY","text_ar":"لَا يَزَالُ النَّاسُ مُخْتَلِفَةً اَعْنَاقُهُمْ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Talabi Ald~unoyaA","text_ar":"طَلَبِ الدُّنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mankind will not cease to have"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their companies"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"parties diverse in the seeking of worldly good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their heads,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chiefs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great ones."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b15-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"of good; (IAar, O, TA;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn Alxubozi","text_ar":"من الخُبْزِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the K being a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn Alxayori","text_ar":"من الخَيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and of property: and of work, whether good or evil. (O.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lifulaAnK EunuqN mina Alxayori","text_ar":"لِفُلَانٍ عُنُقٌ مِنَ الخَيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To such a one pertains a portion of good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, TA.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almuw^a*~inuwna A^aTowala","text_ar":"المُوَذِّنُونَ اَطْوَلَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsi A^aEonaAqFA yawoma AlqiyaAmapi","text_ar":"النَّاسِ اَعْنَاقًا يَوْمَ القِيَامَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, O, K, * TA,) meaning (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The proclaimers of the times of prayer will be"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the most abundant of men in"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"works"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the day of resurrection"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IAar, O, K, TA:) or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chiefs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the Arabs describe such as being long-necked: but it is also related otherwise, i. e.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iEonaAqFA","text_ar":"اـِعْنَاقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr to the hemzeh, meaning, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the most"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hasting"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of men"},{"kind":"text","text":"] to Paradise: (O, K, TA:) and there are other explanations: (K, TA:) one is, that they"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be preceders"},{"kind":"text","text":"to Paradise; from the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu EunuqN","text_ar":"لَهُ عُنُقٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Alxayori","text_ar":"فِى الخَيْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he has precedence in that which is good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says Th: another, that they"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be forgiven to the extent of the prolonging of their voice:"},{"kind":"text","text":"another, that they"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be given an addition above other men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"another, that they"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be in a state of happiness and sprightliness, raising the eyes and looking in expectation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for permission will have been given to them to enter Paradise: and other explanations may be found in the Fáïk and the Nh and the Expositions of Bkh. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuqN","text_ar":"عُنُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also a pl. of the next word. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","K","Sb","S","O","IAar"]}]}}